# System Architecture - Learning Documentation

**Document Purpose**: This document explores the architectural patterns I 
learned while developing Caldera plugins during my Triskele Labs internship.

## Educational Context

This architecture demonstrates my understanding of:
- Plugin-based extensibility patterns
- Event-driven service communication
- Security automation workflows
- Integration with SIEM platforms (ELK Stack)

**Disclaimer**: This architecture was designed as a learning exercise. It has 
not been reviewed for production use, security-hardened for real environments, 
or tested at scale.

## Design Decisions (Learning Rationale)

I chose this architecture to learn:
- **Seven-plugin approach**: To understand modular design and separation of concerns
- **Event-driven patterns**: To practice asynchronous service communication
- **ELK integration**: To gain experience with security data correlation

[Rest of documentation with "I learned..." framing]

