Legal Review Checklist
Before Showing to Senior Leadership

text
# Pre-Presentation Legal Checklist

- [ ] All references to "production" removed or reframed as "development"
- [ ] No claims about "Triskele Labs platform" or "official software"
- [ ] Apache-2.0 license replaced with Educational/Portfolio license
- [ ] Every document has internship/educational disclaimer
- [ ] No client references or service provider language
- [ ] Repository is PRIVATE (not public)
- [ ] README clearly states "internship project"
- [ ] No security vulnerabilities or sensitive data in code
- [ ] No Triskele Labs confidential information exposed
- [ ] Supervisor has reviewed and approved repository content
- [ ] Clear attribution: "by Tony To" not "by Triskele Labs"

## Final Verification Questions

1. **Could someone mistake this for official Triskele Labs software?**
   - If YES → Add more disclaimers

2. **Are there any production/enterprise claims?**
   - If YES → Reword as educational/learning context

3. **Is the license appropriate for portfolio work?**
   - If NO → Use Educational/Portfolio license

4. **Would Triskele Labs be liable for any claims about this code?**
   - If YES → Add stronger disclaimers separating intern work from company

5. **Is it clear this is YOUR work during an internship, not company IP?**
   - If NO → Clarify authorship and context

