## Project Overview

During my internship at Triskele Labs, I explored Caldera plugin development 
by building three custom plugins to understand purple team automation workflows.

**Learning Objectives**:
- Understand Caldera's plugin architecture through hands-on development
- Practice ELK Stack integration for security event correlation
- Develop Python skills in a security automation context
- Build a portfolio piece demonstrating security engineering capabilities

**What I Built**:
- **Orchestrator Plugin**: Event-driven ELK tagging automation
- **Reporting Plugin**: PDF report generation with detection coverage analysis
- **Branding Plugin**: UI customisation exploration

---

## Skills Demonstrated

This project showcases my ability to:
- Develop plugins for security automation frameworks
- Implement event-driven architectures in Python
- Integrate with SIEM platforms (Elasticsearch)
- Generate PDF reports programmatically (ReportLab)
- Write comprehensive technical documentation
- Follow security development best practices

---

## Development Environment Setup

**Intended Users**: Portfolio reviewers, technical interviewers, educators

**Prerequisites**:
- Python 3.9+
- Elasticsearch 8.11+ (for ELK integration testing)
- 8GB RAM (for running Caldera in development mode)

**Quick Start** (Development Environment):
```bash
# Clone repository (private - request access)
git clone https://github.com/L1quidDroid/Internship_C

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

