## Final Recommendations

### Make It Look Professional ✅

**DO**:
- Use clean documentation structure
- Include architecture diagrams
- Show comprehensive testing
- Demonstrate code quality
- Write clear installation guides
- Present well in demos

### But Keep It Educational ✅

**DO**:
- Add disclaimers on every page
- Frame as "learning exercise"
- Use "I learned" language
- Attribute as internship work
- Keep repository PRIVATE
- Use Educational license

### Legal Protection ✅

**DO**:
- Get supervisor approval
- Remove production/client language
- Add strong disclaimers
- Clarify NOT official TL software
- Keep confidential info out
- Use appropriate license

This approach lets you showcase professional-quality work while being legally clear it's an internship project, not production software.
